Do you want to meet some of the top investors and pioneers in the tech industry, such as Steve Wozniak and Una Ryan? Ascend, a premier finance and accounting organization, invites you to attend our case competition co-hosted with Bay Area startup Travonde! 

 

We have two tracks for this case competition: software engineering and marketing. The top three teams will get exclusive office tours and networking lunches with the judges, and additionally, first place will win an Apple watch!

 

Registration is LIVE and will be open until 9/20, apply at tinyurl.com/ascendcasecomp

 

This case competition is open to all Berkeley students, no major or year constraints. Apply as a team of 2-4 people or choose to form a team at the info session on Sept. 16.

 

The final presentation day is open to the public, so feel free to come learn from our finalists’ presentations, network with our judges, and catch an exclusive fireside chat with Steve Wozniak on 9/28!

 

Timeline:

9/15 (Sun) - Case will be released through email

9/16 (Mon) - Info session and Q&A with Travonde professionals*

9/20 (Fri) - Application closes & deliverable due

9/23 (Mon) - Result Release

9/28 (Fri) - Final Presentation and Fireside chat with Steve Wozniak**

 

* Info session is hosted from 8-9PM on September 16th in Moffitt 102.

** Final presentation day will be from 2-5:15pm at 100 GPB, networking session with the judges and fireside chat with Wozniak included.
